Liverpool manager Brendan Rodgers has been convicted of leaving a property to rot after he was fined for the condition of a house he rented out which was left in a state of disrepair for three years .
The Anfield boss was ordered to pay £ 400 and £ 375 costs , with a £ 40 surcharge at Blackburn magistrates ' court for leaving a £ 69,950 terrace house in Accrington with broken windows and doors and rubbish .
Rodgers and his business partner Judith O'Hagan were found guilty of ignoring an improvement notice issued by Hyndburn Council .